# CSS Guidelines

## Principle: antd-first, CSS-last

Only write custom CSS for things antd cannot handle:
- Page container max-width + centering
- Background gradients (e.g., hero sections)
- Image sizing (object-fit, fixed heights)
- Responsive breakpoints for layout shifts

## Do NOT write CSS for

- Text colors, sizes, weights — use antd `Typography`
- Spacing between elements — use antd `Flex`, `Space`
- Card layout, body — use `Card.Meta`
- Button, form, table styles — antd handles these
- Error/empty states — use antd `Result`, `Empty`

## Breakpoints

```css
@media (max-width: 768px)  { /* tablet */ }
@media (max-width: 480px)  { /* mobile */ }
@media (max-width: 992px)  { /* admin sidebar collapse — matches antd lg */ }
```

## No inline styles

Use CSS modules (`.module.css`) when custom styles are needed. Exception: antd `Form` `style={{ maxWidth }}` is acceptable for constraining form width.
